@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{ai-extras.el} provides backend-agnostic abstractions for AI coding CLI tool extensions.  Rather than duplicating common functionality across packages like @samp{claude-code-extras.el} and @samp{codex-extras.el}, this package centralizes shared features such as session management, notifications, terminal integration, and snippet expansion.

The package uses a backend registry with @code{cl-defgeneric} style dispatch.  Each AI tool (Claude Code, Codex, etc.) registers itself as a backend by providing a property list of functions for buffer detection, session enumeration, command sending, and session creation.  All shared features then operate across backends transparently.

Key capabilities include:

@itemize
@item
A unified session switcher with home-row key assignments for quick session access across all registered backends.
@item
An alert and notification system that fires OS notifications when sessions need attention.
@item
Buffer protection to prevent accidental session kills.
@item
Yasnippet integration for expanding snippets at terminal prompts.
@item
Terminal rendering fixes for the @samp{eat} terminal emulator.
@end itemize

@samp{ai-extras.el} depends on @samp{transient} for the session switcher menu and @samp{consult} for completion interfaces.

